          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "- Depleted U-238 sample, diameter 10 mm, thickness",
                "0.3 mm, packed in teflon foil, positioned at 30 deg",
                "angle, irradiated 12 hr , measured several times for",
                "10 min and 1 hr.",
                "Isotopic composition, % :",
                "U-234 - (7.403+-0.018)*10**-4",
                "U-235 - 0.20039+-0.00012",
                "U-236 - (3.1876+-0.0083)*10**-3",
                "U-238 - 99.79568+-0.00012",
                "- NpO(2) powder, Np-237 isotopic abundance 99.5+-0.1 %,",
                "other Np isotopes < 0.7 %. Impurities < 0.1 % .",
                "Pressed to a pellet of 0.2 mm thickness, 3 mm diameter,",
                "imbedded in 40 mm x 40 mm x 0.2 mm quarz blades.",
                "Mass of sample - 3.3399+-0.0018 mg corresponds to",
                " (74.38+-0.05)*10**17 Np-237 atoms.",
                "- 242PuO(2) powder, prepared in the same way as Np",
                "sample.",
                "Isotopic composition, % ( as given by ORNL, 1980 yr):",
                " Pu-238 - 0.004 , Pu-239 - 0.005 , Pu-240 - 0.022 ,",
                " Pu-241 - 0.035 , Pu-242 - 99.93 %, Pu-244 - 0.022 .",
                " Decay during 37 years was then taken into account and",
                " considered to be very low.",
                " Sample mass 9.3034+-0.0052 mg corresponds",
                " (204.29+-0.12)*10**17 Pu-242 atoms."
              ]
            }
